Create multiple tensor fields from a template, distribution.

functions, units, and coordinate system. The concept this multi-field create method provides are... 1. hint to implementation of storing them together, 2. possible convenience for caller to set all dofs together 3. storage is predictable/computable because all fields obey properties that make this possible. This also has implications in array-based methods of getting/setting dofs as well. Have to look into Fortran size requirements here! Restrictions: 1. The resulting component fields can be evaluated and set/getDOF'ed individually, but can't be destroyed individually. 2. All fields must use the same dfunc and data storage precision. 3. Units need not be consistent between fields, as they're each defined separately.

Parameters:
[in] instance iField instance handle
[in] domain_handle The domain this field is defined on.
[in] precision Is this data single precision, double precision, etc? (enum)
[in] dfunc_kernel A function callback for converting spatial coordinates into the value for a distribution function.
[in] tt_handles One tensor template for each tensor to be created.
[in] units_handles Units for each tensor to be created.
[in] names An array of strings giving names of tensors (one more name than templates, so that the compound will also have a name).
[in] num_tensors How many new tensors?
[out] compound_handle A separate handle for the collection of tensors.
[in,out] tensor_handles The new tensor fields.
[in,out] tensor_handles_allocated Allocated size of tensor handle array.
[out] tensor_handles_size Number of tensors created and returned.
[out] err Returned Error status (see iBase_ErrorType)
name_len Lengths of name strings. [CFOG
